From b1c2d3e4f5a6b7c8d9e0f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ret2ldz <ret2ldz@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 13 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Florida: helper-jni-rename

Rename the Android helper's Java package, JNI class refs, and D-Bus
helper interface from `re.frida.*` / `re/frida/*` to `re.ggbond.*` /
`re/ggbond/*` so that apps scanning the helper DEX (embedded in
frida-server) for the `re.frida.Helper` / `re/frida/HelperBackend`
class names no longer match.

This corresponds to PR https://github.com/TheQmaks/phantom-frida/pull/7
which fixed phantom-frida's broken source-level rename (the dot-notation
`re.frida.Helper` had been renamed but the JNI slash-notation
`re/frida/HelperBackend` had not, causing `find_class()` to return null
and crash on the `assert(backend_class != null)` in
`linux-host-session.vala`).

PR #7 only adds the slash-notation rename. For Florida this is the first
time we touch any of these strings, so the patch is broader — it also
renames the dot-notation Java class refs (`re.frida.Helper`,
`re.frida.helper` process name, `re.frida.Gadget` app id), the Java
package declarations (`package re.frida;` -> `package re.ggbond;`), and
the D-Bus helper interface / object path. Without those, the slash-
notation rename alone would break frida (Java package would still be
`re.frida`, but `find_class("re/ggbond/HelperBackend")` would look for
`re.ggbond.HelperBackend` which doesn't exist).

What is renamed consistently:
  - Java package declaration (`package re.frida;` -> `package re.ggbond;`)
  - Java class refs in dot-notation (Makefile jar entry, meson.build,
    droidy spawn args, fruity/droidy GADGET_APP_ID, gadget.vala
    identifier)
  - JNI class ref in slash-notation (find_class call in
    linux-host-session.vala)
  - D-Bus helper interface name (`re.frida.Helper` -> `re.ggbond.Helper`)
  - D-Bus helper object path (`/re/frida/Helper` -> `/re/ggbond/Helper`)
  - Helper process nice-name (`--nice-name=re.frida.helper` -> `--nice-name=re.ggbond.helper`)

What is NOT renamed (intentional):
  - `re.frida.HostSession17` / `re.frida.AgentSession17` / etc. — these
    are the client-server D-Bus wire protocol, renaming breaks the
    unpatched `pip install frida-tools` client. phantom-frida also
    leaves these alone.
  - `/re/frida/HostSession` etc. — D-Bus object paths for the
    client-facing protocol. Same reason.
  - File paths `re/frida/Helper.java` in Makefile — these are file system
    paths, not Java identifiers. Java allows the source file path to
    differ from the package, so the .java files stay at
    `src/android-helper/re/frida/` while declaring `package re.ggbond;`.
    The compiled .class lands at `build/java/re/ggbond/Helper.class`
    regardless of source file location.
  - `re.frida.server` (server.vala DEFAULT_DIRECTORY) — separate vector,
    not part of PR #7.
  - Darwin-only files (`frida-helper.xcent`, `frida-helper.plist`,
    `frida-helper-backend-glue.m`) — not built for Android, skipped.

Merged from https://github.com/TheQmaks/phantom-frida PR #7 + the
prerequisite dot-notation renames from get_source_patches.

